# Universal Inc. — Prompt Engineering Reference

## 1. Feature: AI Tattoo Generation (Paid Clients)

Since you are using React 19 and tRPC, we will implement this by connecting to a GenAI API (like Gemini 1.5 Flash or Stable Diffusion via Replicate/OpenAI).

### A. Backend: tRPC AI Router (`backend/server/routers/ai.ts`)

We use a Zod schema to validate the prompt and ensure only paid clients can hit this endpoint.

```typescript
import { z } from "zod";
import { router, protectedProcedure } from "../_core/trpc";
import { TRPCError } from "@trpc/server";

export const aiRouter = router({
  generateDesign: protectedProcedure
    .input(z.object({
      prompt: z.string().min(10),
      style: z.string().optional(),
    }))
    .mutation(async ({ ctx, input }) => {
      // 1. Fetch the client record (subscriptionTier lives on the clients table)
      const client = await ctx.db.query.clients.findFirst({
        where: (c, { eq }) => eq(c.userId, ctx.user.id),
      });

      if (!client || client.subscriptionTier === 'free') {
        throw new TRPCError({
          code: "FORBIDDEN",
          message: "AI Generation is a premium feature. Please upgrade your plan.",
        });
      }

      // 2. Verify AI credits before calling the service
      if (client.subscriptionTier === 'enthusiast' && client.aiCredits <= 0) {
        throw new TRPCError({
          code: "FORBIDDEN",
          message: "You have used all your AI generation credits for this billing period.",
        });
      }

      // 3. Call AI Service
      // TODO: Replace with actual AI service call, e.g.:
      //   const { imageUrl, meta } = await generateImage(serviceClient, input.prompt);
      // Wrap in try/catch to handle and log errors.
      let imageUrl: string;
      try {
        const result = await generateImage(serviceClient, input.prompt);
        imageUrl = result.imageUrl;
      } catch (err) {
        console.error("AI generation failed:", err);
        throw new TRPCError({
          code: "INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR",
          message: "Failed to generate image. Please try again.",
        });
      }

      // 4. Deduct an AI credit for paid (non-unlimited) tiers
      if (client.subscriptionTier === 'enthusiast') {
        await ctx.db.update(clients)
          .set({ aiCredits: client.aiCredits - 1 })
          .where(eq(clients.id, client.id));
      }

      return { imageUrl };
    }),
});
```

### B. Frontend: Generation UI (`frontend/client/src/components/AIGenerator.tsx`)

Following the 150-line rule and using shadcn/ui Skeletons.

```typescript
import { useState } from "react";
import { trpc } from "../lib/trpc";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Skeleton } from "@/components/ui/skeleton";
import { Sparkles } from "lucide-react"; // Use lucide-react as per rules

export function AIGenerator() {
  const [prompt, setPrompt] = useState("");
  const generate = trpc.ai.generateDesign.useMutation({
    onError: (error) => {
      // Surface API errors to the user
      setError(error.message || "Generation failed. Please try again.");
    },
  });
  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);

  return (
    <div className="space-y-4 p-6 border rounded-xl bg-card">
      <h3 className="text-lg font-bold flex items-center gap-2">
        <Sparkles className="w-5 h-5 text-primary" />
        AI Design Lab
      </h3>

      <textarea
        className="w-full p-3 rounded-md bg-background border"
        placeholder="Describe your tattoo (e.g., 'A geometric wolf with watercolor splashes on the shoulder')..."
        value={prompt}
        onChange={(e) => setPrompt(e.target.value)}
      />

      {generate.isLoading ? (
        <Skeleton className="w-full h-[300px] rounded-lg" />
      ) : generate.data?.imageUrl ? (
        <img src={generate.data.imageUrl} className="w-full rounded-lg" alt="Generated" />
      ) : null}

      {error && (
        <p className="text-sm text-destructive">{error}</p>
      )}

      <Button
        onClick={() => {
          setError(null);
          generate.mutate({ prompt });
        }}
        disabled={generate.isLoading || prompt.length < 10}
      >
        {generate.isLoading ? "Inking..." : "Generate Concept"}
      </Button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

